                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180114-104-off549 t18180114-104-crimeloc552"></join>. On the 3d of January, about half-past six o'clock in the evening, I heard a noise at the door, and looking towards a pile of goods, I missed a bundle of stuff that was on it-it was about two feet from the door. I immediately saw some person pass the window with it. I went out, and secured the prisoner with the goods under his arm. He said, "Let me go, as you have got your goods. He resisted very much.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 26.</p>
